        },

            "reference": "According to McCaig (2010 ), a research desig n is an overarching strategy for unearthing useful",

        },
        {
            "reference": "answers to research problems. This entails that a specific problem will attract the use of a type of",

        },
        {
            "reference": "research design that will address that specific problem. Therefore the researcher found it fit to",

            "reference": "use a descriptive survey design in conducting this research.  Bless and Achola (1988) define a",

        {
            "reference": "descriptive survey design as a mode of collecting information by interviewing or administering a",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
        },

            "reference": "questionnaire to a sample of individuals. Since the research sought to  collect information about",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
        },
        {
            "reference": "the respondents\u2019 opinions on the topic at hand, the descriptive research design was ideal. This",

        },
        {
            "reference": "design makes extensive use of primary data such that its use in this study privileges the voices of",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
        },
        {
            "reference": "young girls and considers their v iews alongside those of their teachers and parents so as to",

        },

            "reference": "analyse their perceptions of the re -entry policy in relation to the girl\u2019s behaviour. The study used",

        },
        {
            "reference": "both quantitative and qualitative methods of data collection. In this case,  the questionnaire a nd",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
        },
        {
            "reference": "intervie ws were  employed  to collect data which validated each other and this is referred to as",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
        },
        {
            "reference": "triangulation. It is a methodological rule that should be used in every investigation (Denzin,",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
        },
        {
            "reference": "1978). This is so because as a strategy it provides ways of cap turing information by one method",
            "apa_check": "Not in APA style"
